                          "fill": "$--foreground",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Background. Theta oscillations have long been implicated in rodent spatial memory; whether they serve the same role in humans remained debated (Buzsáki 2019; Herweg 2020).\n\nMethods. 17 drug-resistant epilepsy patients (6 F, age 22–48) performed a free-recall task during intracranial recordings. 132 microwire contacts in CA1–CA3. Phase-locking indices (PLI) computed per unit vs. local theta.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.7,
                          "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Serif",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
